#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn36.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Aṭṭhasatapariyāyavagga "
msgstr "3. The Explanation of the Hundred and Eight "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 21. Sīvakasutta → moḷiyasīvakasuttaṃ (bj) | sīvako (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Sīvakasutta "
msgstr "21. With Sīvaka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.230, sc1
msgctxt "sn36.21:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.21:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho moḷiyasīvako paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then the wanderer Moḷiyasīvaka went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "sn36.21:1.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho moḷiyasīvako paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.21:1.4"
msgid "“santi, bho gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, there are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view: "

msgctxt "sn36.21:1.5"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñcāyaṃ purisapuggalo paṭisaṃvedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā sabbaṃ taṃ pubbekatahetū’ti. "
msgstr "‘Everything this individual experiences—pleasurable, painful, or neutral—is because of past deeds.’ "

#. VAR: Idha → idha pana (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn36.21:1.6"
msgid "Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti? "
msgstr "What does Master Gotama say about this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn36.21:2.1"
msgid "“Pittasamuṭṭhānānipi kho, sīvaka, idhekaccāni vedayitāni uppajjanti. "
msgstr "“Sīvaka, some feelings stem from bile disorders. "

#. VAR: sīvaka, veditabbaṃ → evaṃ veditabbaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn36.21:2.2"
msgid "Sāmampi kho etaṃ, sīvaka, veditabbaṃ yathā pittasamuṭṭhānānipi idhekaccāni vedayitāni uppajjanti. "
msgstr "You can know this from your own personal experience, "

msgctxt "sn36.21:2.3"
msgid "Lokassapi kho etaṃ, sīvaka, saccasammataṃ yathā pittasamuṭṭhānānipi idhekaccāni vedayitāni uppajjanti. "
msgstr "and it is generally agreed to be true. "

msgctxt "sn36.21:2.4"
msgid "Tatra, sīvaka, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: "
msgstr "Since this is so, the ascetics and brahmins whose view is that "

msgctxt "sn36.21:2.5"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñcāyaṃ purisapuggalo paṭisaṃvedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā sabbaṃ taṃ pubbekatahetū’ti. "
msgstr "everything an individual experiences is because of past deeds "

msgctxt "sn36.21:2.6"
msgid "Yañca sāmaṃ ñātaṃ tañca atidhāvanti, yañca loke saccasammataṃ tañca atidhāvanti. "
msgstr "go beyond personal experience and beyond what is generally agreed to be true. "

msgctxt "sn36.21:2.7"
msgid "Tasmā tesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ micchāti vadāmi. "
msgstr "So those ascetics and brahmins are wrong, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.231, sc3
msgctxt "sn36.21:3.1"
msgid "Semhasamuṭṭhānānipi kho, sīvaka … pe … "
msgstr "Some feelings stem from phlegm disorders … "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.2"
msgid "vātasamuṭṭhānānipi kho, sīvaka … pe … "
msgstr "wind disorders … "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.3"
msgid "sannipātikānipi kho, sīvaka … pe … "
msgstr "their conjunction … "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.4"
msgid "utupariṇāmajānipi kho, sīvaka … pe … "
msgstr "change in weather … "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.5"
msgid "visamaparihārajānipi kho, sīvaka … pe … "
msgstr "not taking care of yourself … "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.6"
msgid "opakkamikānipi kho, sīvaka … pe … "
msgstr "overexertion … "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.7"
msgid "kammavipākajānipi kho, sīvaka, idhekaccāni vedayitāni uppajjanti. "
msgstr "Some feelings are the result of past deeds. "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.8"
msgid "Sāmampi kho etaṃ, sīvaka, veditabbaṃ. "
msgstr "You can know this from your own personal experience, "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.9"
msgid "Yathā kammavipākajānipi idhekaccāni vedayitāni uppajjanti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.10"
msgid "lokassapi kho etaṃ, sīvaka, saccasammataṃ. "
msgstr "and it is generally agreed to be true. "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.11"
msgid "Yathā kammavipākajānipi idhekaccāni vedayitāni uppajjanti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.12"
msgid "tatra, sīvaka, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: "
msgstr "Since this is so, the ascetics and brahmins whose view is that "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.13"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñcāyaṃ purisapuggalo paṭisaṃvedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā sabbaṃ taṃ pubbekatahetū’ti. "
msgstr "everything an individual experiences is because of past deeds "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.14"
msgid "Yañca sāmaṃ ñātaṃ tañca atidhāvanti yañca loke saccasammataṃ tañca atidhāvanti. "
msgstr "go beyond personal experience and beyond what is generally agreed to be true. "

msgctxt "sn36.21:3.15"
msgid "Tasmā ‘tesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ micchā’ti vadāmī”ti. "
msgstr "So those ascetics and brahmins are wrong, I say.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn36.21:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, moḷiyasīvako paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, the wanderer Moḷiyasīvaka said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn36.21:4.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! … "

msgctxt "sn36.21:4.3"
msgid "upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn36.21:5.1"
msgid "“Pittaṃ semhañca vāto ca, "
msgstr "“Bile, phlegm, and wind, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.21:5.2"
msgid "Sannipātā utūni ca; "
msgstr "their conjunction, and the weather, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.21:5.3"
msgid "Visamaṃ opakkamikaṃ, "
msgstr "not taking care of yourself, overexertion, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.21:5.4"
msgid "Kammavipākena aṭṭhamī”ti. "
msgstr "and the result of deeds is the eighth.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.21:5.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
